"<i class=\"fa fa-exclamation-triangle text-danger me-2\"/> <strong>Strict "
"Validation:</strong> The system <strong>rejects</strong> KRS submissions if:"
" (1) SKS exceeds the GPA limit, (2) Schedule conflicts, (3) Class quota is "
"full, or (4) Student has not passed the prerequisite subjects."
msgstr ""

#. module: campus_core
#: model_terms:ir.ui.view,arch_db:campus_core.core_homepage_docs
msgid ""
"<i class=\"fa fa-flash text-info me-2\"/> <strong>Action (Generate "
"KRS):</strong> Click \"Generate KRS\" on the Package, and the system will "
"filter students of that program who have not created KRS. Check dozens of "
"student names, and mass <em>Draft KRS</em> (with their subject lines) will "
"be issued in the blink of an eye!"
msgstr ""

#. module: campus_core
#: model_terms:ir.ui.view,arch_db:campus_core.core_homepage_docs
msgid ""
"<i class=\"fa fa-info-circle text-info me-2\"/> <strong>Note:</strong> This "
"period restriction <strong>only applies to Students</strong> (Portal users)."
" Academic Admin can create or edit KRS anytime without being bound by the "
"period, assisting students who cannot fill it themselves."
msgstr ""

#. module: campus_core
#: model_terms:ir.ui.view,arch_db:campus_core.core_homepage_docs
msgid ""
"<i class=\"fa fa-info-circle text-info me-2\"/> <strong>Smart Note:</strong>"
" The system automatically skips lines with mismatching status. For example, "
"if you check 10 KRS and select <em>Mass Approve</em>, only KRS in Submitted "
"status will be processed; Draft KRS will remain untouched."
msgstr ""

